# Next.js App Router API Route Guidelines

# Route Parameters
- Always include all route parameters in the type definition:
  ```typescript
  { params }: { params: { moveId: string; layoutId: string } }
  ```
- Validate parameters exist before using them
- Return 400 error if parameters are missing

# Request Validation
- Use zod for validation
- Validate all required fields
- Return 400 error for validation failures

# Error Handling
- Use consistent error format:
  ```typescript
  {
    success: false,
    error: {
      message: string,
      code: string
    }
  }
  ```

# Response Format
- Use consistent success format:
  ```typescript
  {
    success: true,
    data: any
  }
  ```

# Type Safety
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Never use any
- Use type guards for runtime checks

# Additional Guidelines
- Always validate request body exists
- Validate required fields match schema
- Use proper error responses (400 for validation, 401 for auth, 404 for not found)
- Include descriptive error messages
- Include all necessary relations in response
- Handle unique constraints properly
- Match all schema fields exactly
- Handle optional fields correctly
- Respect default values
- Include all required relations
- Never modify schema to match code - always adapt code to match schema
- Use exact field names from schema
- Handle type conversions properly
- Use try/catch blocks
- Log errors with context
- Return appropriate status codes
- Include error details in response
- Use consistent error response format
- Use consistent response structure
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Check session in every route
- Verify user access to resources
- Handle unauthorized access properly
- Use consistent auth error format
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Validate input types
- Handle type conversions properly
- Use type guards for runtime type checking
- Never use any type
- Use proper type mapping between frontend and backend 